    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it compulsory for councils to have zebra crossings outside every school",
        "additional_details": "I think that not enough is done for road safety of our children. Lollipop ladies don\u2019t seem to exist anymore and where we are in a rural town road safety isn\u2019t consider necessary by Kent County Council they insist on a number of incidents occurring or a fatality. It shouldn\u2019t take something to happen for precautions to be in place. There should be a zebra crossing outside every school!",
        "background": "Road Safety around children should be compulsory and precautions outside every school regardless of incidents. If there\u2019s children crossing we need to keep them safe at all costs.",
